Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @Tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}; finely chop a few
slices until you have 2 TBSP. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Halve, deseed, and finely
chop @Jalapeño{1}. (TIP: Leave seeds in for more spice!) Peel and finely chop
@Garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water
(1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, chopped onion, half the lime
zest, a squeeze of lime juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, and as much jalapeño as
you like.

Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
sliced onion and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Chopped Chicken Breast{10%ounce}, garlic, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon},
and another big pinch of salt. TIP: If you like things spicy, add any remaining
jalapeño.

Using a #spatula{}, arrange chicken into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until
browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up into pieces; cook, stirring
occasionally, until chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.
TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

To pan with chicken, stir in @Tomato Paste{1} and @Beef Stock Concentrate{1},
then add ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Cook until slightly thickened,
~{1-2%minutes} more.

Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted; turn off heat.

While chicken cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}
with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a
time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining lime zest and @Butter{1%tablespoon}
(2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with chicken mixture, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup},
salsa, and crema. Serve with @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining
lime wedges on the side.